  "SoftBank has forecast an annual loss of $6.9 billion, its first in 15 years, and a $16.7 billion investment loss in its $100 billion Vision Fund, for the year ending March 2020.",
  "Investors in Son's Vision Fund include Apple, Qualcomm, Foxconn, the family office of billionaire Larry Ellison and Saudi Arabia's sovereign fund.",
  "The Vision Fund has invested in 88 companies, including ride-share firm Grab,  Korean ecommerce leader Coupang and India's Paytm.",
  "SoftBank's shares, which fell after the WeWork IPO collapsed in 2019, were up in 2020 thanks to IPOs such as that of food delivery firm DoorDash."
